text.tspan: Conceptualization
The knowledge formalization starts with a conceptualization
i.e., the identification of objects and
their relationships which are presumed or assumed
to exist in the world.
In this section, we will describe how the knowledge
is formalized and stored in the graph database
and Knowledge base of the system.
Graph database
The structure of the Database is composed of nodes
and edges which are the result of the triples
extraction provided by the system ( e.g ["William
henry gates iii", "per:title", "magnate" ]).
Given a triple, the two subjects are formalized as
nodes and the relation is an edge between the
nodes.
The graph is composed of a set of nodes, each of which
as the following structure:
Identity
: number which identifies the nodes in the
graph.
labels
: each node is associated with a label that
identifies the type of node; the label is given
by the Name Entity Recognition, if the system has
recognized the entity (e.g person,
organization, title etc.); otherwise only the label
“o”, as Object, is given.
properties
name:
the string of the SRO triples extracted (e.g
“William henry gates iii”).
id:
identification number of the data structure used
to store the entity in the
program before being stored in the database.
type
: the label of the node.
The edges of the graph are created following the relation
of the SRO triples and they have the
following structure:
Identity
: number which identifies the edge in the
graph.
start
: identification number of the subject node
end
: identification number of the object node.
type
: string value
of the relationship (e.g title).
properties
start:
identification number of the data structure
used to store the entity in the
program before being stored in the database of the
start node.
end:
identification number of the data structure used
to store the entity in the
program before being stored in the database of the
end node.
type:
string value of the relationship (e.g title).
Each relation has a string which contains the topic
of the relation (e.g “per:title”). The string of
the
topic starts with “per:” if the first subject is a
person, “org:” if the subject is considered an
organization/company (e.g with “per:title” the kbp
has recognized “William henry gates iii” has a
person).
